"7016A0507001 Ver: 1.00" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos.
This is the same text found on the [[WatchGuard AP100]] :(''[[Senao]]'' CAP2100AG) and the [[Senao CAP4200AG]]. A label affixed to BSAP-1920 model (integral antennas) :in FCC photos identifies the device as a CAP4200AG.
*5GHz radio (AR9344) - 2x ''[[Skyworks]]'' (''[[SiGe]]'') [http://www.skyworksinc.com/Product.aspx?ProductID=944 SE2537L] Power Amplifier *2.4GHz radio (AR9382) - 2x ''[[Microchip]]'' (''[[SST]]'') [https://www.microchip.com/wwwproducts/Devices.aspx?dDocName=en550350 SST12LP15A] Power Amplifier
The default credentials in this entry are per the FCC QSG. :They are specified as being for SSH access.
===PSU=== The power adapter shown in the FCC external photos is a '''Powertron Electronics''' PA1015-2I :PA1015-2I 120125 (100-240VAC ~ 50-60Hz, 0.4A -> 12VDC, 1.25A, 15W max.).
